It seems that [DateInterval](https://react-day-picker.js.org/api/types/DateInterval) is not handled correctly in [isMatch](https://github.com/gpbl/react-day-picker/blob/5b9f24b7abbcab507c73f619d2446a671505d680/packages/react-day-picker/src/contexts/Modifiers/utils/isMatch.ts#L60-L64):

https://github.com/gpbl/react-day-picker/blob/5b9f24b7abbcab507c73f619d2446a671505d680/packages/react-day-picker/src/contexts/Modifiers/utils/isMatch.ts#L60-L64

I agree it is confusing. As alternative:

```tsx
disabled={[
  { after: new Date() },
  { before: new Date(new Date().getTime() - 10 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000) }
]}
}
```

[codesandbox](https://codesandbox.io/s/react-daypicker-forked-9mr6rr)

